def: Like fish; suggestive of fish; having some of the qualities offish.A very ancient and fishlike smell. Shak.
A genus of marine gastropods having a long, tapering spire.They belong to the Toxoglossa. Called also auger shell.
One who envies; one who desires inordinately what anotherpossesses.
A want of grammatical sequence or coherence in a sentence; aninstance of a change of construction in a sentence so that the latterpart does not syntactically correspond with the first part.
A trader in law; one who practices law as if it were a trade.Milton.
To hasten; to hurry. [Archaic]I 'll haste the writer. Shak.They were troubled and hasted away. Ps. xlviii. 5.
One skilled in the theory or use of torpedoes; also, one whofavors the use of torpedoes.

To extend through the same space or time with another; toextend to the same degree.According to which the least body may be coextended with thegreatest. Boyle.Has your English language one single word that is coextended throughall these significations Bentley.
